OL,3,CAmber weather warnings in place for
OL,4,Cparts of Wales
OL,6,FThe Met Office has issued an amber
OL,7,Fweather warning for heavy rain across
OL,8,Flarge parts of Wales, describing
OL,9,Fconditions that pose a "danger to
OL,10,Flife" as Storm Bram is set to hit the
OL,11,FUK in the coming days.
OL,13,FYellow weather warnings for wind and
OL,14,Frain are in place for much of Wales
OL,15,Ffrom this evening until tomorrow
OL,16,Fafternoon.
OL,18,FThis additional amber warning for rain
OL,19,Fis in place from midnight until 10am
OL,20,Ftomorrow, as Storm Bram is expected to
OL,21,Fcause flooding and travel disruption.
