OL,3,CAmber weather warnings in place for
OL,4,Cparts of Wales
OL,6,FCharlotte Morgan, Natural Resources
OL,7,FWales' Duty Tactical Manager, said:
OL,8,F"We are expecting to see very large
OL,9,Fwaves and are advising people to stay
OL,10,Fclear of promenades and seafronts as
OL,11,Fyou could be swept away by large waves
OL,12,For hit by debris.
OL,14,F"Our thoughts are with those
OL,15,Fcommunities who have recently been
OL,16,Fimpacted, and they could potentially
OL,17,Fbe impacted again during this event."
